      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@promag Would you mind re-reviewing? One way to make the Clang thread safety analysis machinery happy without changing behaviour seems to be to repeat the locking of the recursive mutex `pwallet->cs_wallet` with a lock in the `if (pwallet)` scope as well.  That inner scope lock is technically redundant. Let me know if you find a cleaner way to do it.",
